other_tests.findings: The appendix is dilated to 9 mm with hyperemic wall and fluid filled with mild surrounding stranding consistent with appendicitis. The imaged lung bases demonstrate bibasilar atelectasis without pleural or pericardial effusion. The liver is normal in attenuation, and the gallbladder is surgically absent. The kidneys enhance and excrete contrast symmetrically without hydronephrosis. No mesenteric or retroperitoneal lymphadenopathy aside from mild right lower quadrant reactive lymph node enlargement.
